Hi all, if anyone can help with a curious question, i would appreciate it. Its sort of awkward to describe. I’ve tried to ask before and made a hash of it... So please laugh quietly if i have ruined it again...

Anyway... Pause at Stage Separation at 38:56... On the right of the split screen is the second stage about to fire. On the most far right of the entire screen is a ”foil” looking thing, that appears to enclose some of the engine body.

Okay, press play and watch that ”foil” .

Admittedly the effect is not so much on this particular launch. However, on other launches it seems to start somewhat deflated and then suddenly inflate when it fires up... On this launch it still seems to balloon up a little...

Anyone got any idea whats going on there?

My thoughts, if you fancy that laugh...

- It is there to protect from radiant heat from the flamey end and potentially the suns rays...

- Maybe it does inflate with some tiny amount of gas to maintain an insulation layer...

- That could explain why it seems to be a loose fitting bag that inflates.

- I would have not expected it to be air tight with reflectance being its only job...

- I cant even be sure if there is any gas in it at this altitude and the whole thing is not just a weird inertial effect of acceleration on the foil...

Smarter people than I of the venerable inter webs, please help... or at least speculate wildly until one shows up... thanks.
